Gombe State Governor, Alhaji Muhammadu Inuwa Yahaya has felicitated with his Kaduna State counterpart, Malam Nasir Ahmad El-Rufa’i as he turns 60. In a goodwill message he personally signed and release by his senior special assistant (Media and Publicity), Ismaila Uba Misilli, Governor Yahaya commended the tenacity and unwavering commitment of Malam  El-Rufa’i in the execution of developmental projects and programmes in his state. He noted that “Your pedigree of excellence, tenacity,  courage and remarkable performance have stood you out and made you a reference point of good governance and positive transformation. “I join the good people of Kaduna State and indeed millions of your well wishers in celebrating your attainment of three scores which is a great milestone in life worthy of celebration.” He lauded the governor for using his good office to impact positively on the lives of many and well as for his strive to restore the lost glory of Kaduna state. The Gombe governor prayed Almighty Allah to continue to bless Governor El- Rufa’i with good health, wisdom and long life to keep serving the fatherland and humanity. 